rComments: He is a fantastic prof. He really cares for his students and his expectations are very clear. If you do what you are asked then you are almost guaranteed an A. He wants his students to succeed and he is willing to talk outside of class and through email to clear things up. His accent isn't an issue and he's easy to understand. Totally recommend
He's the best professor. Follow the requirements and you'll get an A+. I don't know why his rating is so low.
Un des meilleurs prof que j'ai eu! Super gentil et très flexible. Il explique vraiment bien et il donne beaucoup d'exemples

As a first year prof, I hated the guy. As a 4th year prof, Ivanov is literally my best friend. He works better with smaller groups and is more approachable in upper year classes. I think he's better suited for those! Honestly, his PR classes are so easy and so much fun. Regretted my first year with him but not my 4th!

Loved him! I had him in two classes, he's one of my favourite teachers. He's passionate about his teaching and he knows what he's talking about. He takes the attendance, but I also strongly suggest attending anyways. He gives a lot of examples and the content is easier to understand if you're there. Easy grader if you understand and pay attention!
As an immersion student I wouldn't recommend taking this course. Readings were on tests but not discussed in class. Tests were all multiple choice

Le meilleur professeur que j'ai eu de tout mon parcours universitaire! Ne portez pas attention aux commentaires négatifs. Il est passionné & expert dans le domaine. Ses cours (séminaires) sont des incontournables pour les étudiants en RP & CMN. Il faut mettre l'effort en cours mais les bonnes notes sont atteignables. Il tient bcp à ses étudiants!
WORST OF THE WORST, He's very unclear, he takes attendance every class and a very tough grader. Avoid this prof is the best advice i can give !!!!

DO NOT take if you are in French Immersion. Uses France French vocabulary& has a thick accent. Powerpoint slides are very long/crowded. Exam questions are subjective. Will test you on readings (chooses random&irrelevant questions from them).The material got more interesting towards the end of the semester. However, he does care about his students.

Trust me on this and please avoid this prof!! Worst thing was that I could barely understand him (im a native french speaker). Not only a thick accent but does not articulate.. 3 midterms (last one was just a few days before the final lol) and questions are written for you to fail. Had to work hard to get my grade up after the first midterm.

His exams are super tricky and he will often add things to his powerpoint for those who show up to class. So if you miss class and base yourself off the powerpoint he uploads online, you'll be missing a lot of stuff. He also enjoys using extremely complicated and complex vocabulary that most students in an introduction course don't understand. 0/5
Sometimes is very unclear.

Vous pouvez facilement manquer les cours, et les récupérer via les slides brightspace. Les midterms sont difficiles, les questions, tricks af. Beaucoup de lectures. Il nomme les gens au début du cours..
Horrible prof! Grades super hard, lectures are boring! Makes a 10 pages paper worth 50% of your grade which is completely stupid! Would not take one of his class again !

Not great. His midterm questions are often subjective. Make sure to sleep before class, or you will fall asleep during his lectures. It is often unclear what he thinks is important, and his readings often have little relevance to the lectures. This class is especially difficult if you're in french immersion, however I did find that it got easier.
Not a very good prof, hard to pay attention in class. His questions on the tests are so specific getting a good grade often comes down to a roll of the dice. Take a different prof for this class.

he's not exactly the best prof but the class is very easy. don't bother buying the textbook, he has a "À retenir" slide at the end of each powerpoint and that is essentially what the 3 midterms and the final are based on. Super easy class, not so good prof.  It really is an easy A. No need to pay attention in class, but show up for attendance
The only way to get a good grade with this teacher is really learning the slides by heart. His questions are really tricky, so beware.
Just dont take his class, take my word for it.

Le cours est intéressant, il y a cependant beaucoup de matière à apprendre. Le professeur est toujours ouvert aux questions, encourage la participation et fait attention à ce que les élèves se sentent bien dans son cours. Les QCM sont parfois un peu sournois, mais une bonne attention et concentration permettent de les réussir assez facilement.

Boring lectures, but he makes an effort to make them interesting and is open to criticism. Three super easy midterms (I barely studied and was in the 80s) and all the questions come directly from the PowerPoints that he puts on Blackboard. Don't buy the textbook!!!

Yes, there are trick questions on the tests, but he takes the critics and the exams are less and less tricky. Yes, you have to read and they are not on the exams, but they complete the course well and they explain a lot of details that you wouldn't have otherwise. A big plus is that he is available if you want to talk to him.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: worst class ever. he does attendance every class (he calls out 5 random names every class). very boring class to attend. midterms were all trick questions, you fail no matter how hard you study. avoid taking him!!!!!
This man cannot take critism while we correct midterms!!!!!!!! Gets defensive and sassy.

Very hard to understand and mumbles often during lectures. He expects you to do lots of readings even though they are not on the exam. Exams are all multiple choice and full of trick questions, his lectures are vague and do not help when it comes to studying for the exams. Overall very disappointed with him as a prof
Try to avoid him at all costs. The notes are extremely vague, and the tests are very specific. I studied very hard for this class, and barely passed.
Uses extraneous words, hard to understand what he says. His tests are much more complicated than the slides. Good luck yall.

Talks so fast you don't understand, mumbles often, gives exams full of trick questions, concepts aren't very clear, doesn't explain well, makes you feel stupid for asking questions even though he tells you to ask questions, makes you read so much before every lecture,  do not recommend!!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Talks very fast and is very unclear. Tests are multiple choice but include lots of trick questions. He asks for feedback but then gets very defensive and does not seem to really change anything. I took this course for french immersion and it was definitely NOT a good choice. Unless you're a native french speaker, DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE.

Talks very fast, leaves little room for descriptive notes. Very good teaching method, nice guy, but hard to understand at times. All mid-terms and final exam are multiple choice questions but the questions are very tricky and the answers almost always look similar. If you work hard, this class shouldn't be too hard.
